******
[2] Alberta and Saskatchewan: commercial flocks
Date: Mon 26 Sep 2022
Source:WattPoultry.com [abridged, edited]
https://www.wattagnet.com/articles/45857-avian-flu-strikes-in-south-dakota-alberta-saskatchewan


Two new cases [of avian influenza] have been reported in Canada, affecting commercial flocks in the provinces of Alberta and Saskatchewan.

The Alberta case was confirmed on 23 Sep [2022] in the municipal district of Willow Creek, reported the Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA). One day later, the presence HPAI was confirmed in another commercial flock in the rural municipality of Britannia, Saskatchewan. CFIA did not disclose details about the flock types or sizes.

So far in September [2022], Alberta has had 11 commercial poultry flocks affected by HPAI, while Saskatchewan has had 4 confirmed cases.

[Byline: Roy Graber]

